body:
I am also experiencing what @mikeymckay is reporting. I can create admins, but when I attempt to use them to create a user:

```
curl -X PUT http://localhost:5984/_users/org.couchdb.user:jan \ ;; subsititing my values
     -H "Accept: application/json" \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{"name": "jan", "password": "apple", "roles": [], "type": "user"}'
```

I receive: `{"error":"unknown_error","reason":"undefined"}`, running an add user from Fauxton also fails, as does verifying the installation on step `Create View`.

I have a suspicion that this is a problem with the "Bitnami" side of things, though that's only a guess.

